---
import Chapter from "@/layouts/Chapter.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Articles/Header.astro";
import Picture from "@/components/Picture.astro";
import Prose from "@/components/Articles/Prose.astro";
import Keyword from "@/components/Articles/Keyword.astro";
import Technologies from "./_components/Technologies.astro";
import Screenshots from "./_components/Screenshots.astro";
---

<Chapter title="Introduction">
  <div class="px-1 md:w-3/4 lg:w-2/3 flex flex-col items-center">
    <Header year="2025" readingTime="5 minutes">
      From Paper to Platform: Engineering Academic Operations at Scale
    </Header>

    <Picture
      class="appear w-full sm:w-3/4 aspect-square sm:aspect-video border-4"
      loading="eager"
      src="/images/learning.webp"
      alt="redis"
      size={514}
    />
  </div>
  <Prose>
    <p>
      A local conglomerate schools in my home-town were managing student
      <strong>records</strong>, <strong>grades</strong>, and <strong
        >subject notes</strong
      > through <Keyword word="Excel" /> spreadsheets that broke constantly. When
      they did, staff had to wait days for someone to fix them, <strong
        >blocking</strong
      > the entire workflow.
    </p>

    <p>
      Uploading the notes for a single subject could take a <strong
        >full day</strong
      >. Generating a student report had to be assembled manually every time —
      slow, error-prone, and exhausting at the end of each period.
    </p>

    <p>
      They platform needed to automate all of this. The catch: deployment
      targets were small school servers, with no dedicated IT team. It had to be
      <strong>easy to deploy</strong>, cheap to run, and maintenance-free.
    </p>

    <h3 class="fraunces">The Stack</h3>

    <Technologies />

    <p>
      This stack was chosen because the system should be as <strong
        >small</strong
      > and <strong>self-contained</strong> as possible. <Keyword word="Go" /> compiles
      to a single static binary and <Keyword word="SQLite" /> runs embedded, allowing
      the <Keyword word="Docker" /> image of just
      <strong>30 MB</strong>.
    </p>

    <h3 class="fraunces">What It Does</h3>

    <p>
      The Staff manages <strong>students</strong>, <strong>subjects</strong>,
      and <strong>notes</strong> through a structured interface. The platform understands
      the relationships between all of them which enable to generate the <strong
        >student notes report</strong
      > automatically.
    </p>

    <h3 class="fraunces">Before and After</h3>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th></th>
          <th>Before</th>
          <th>After</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Upload notes for all subjects</td>
          <td><strong>~1 day</strong> per subject</td>
          <td><strong>~1 hour</strong> total</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Generate student report</td>
          <td><strong>Hand-crafted</strong> manually</td>
          <td><strong>Instant</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>System reliability</td>
          <td>Spreadsheets breaking, <strong>days of downtime</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Always up</strong></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3 class="fraunces">Screenshots of the Project:</h3>

    <Screenshots />
  </Prose>
</Chapter>
